15/10/2009
NEW YORK, United States -- UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon will present a report Thursday (October 15th) to the Security Council on the situation in Kosovo. Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic will attend the meeting, as will Kosovo counterpart Skender Hyseni. Ban is expected to praise UNMIK's role in promoting dialogue and co-operation among the communities in Kosovo, as well as co-operation between Pristina and Belgrade. (Beta, Tanjug - 15/10/09; Medjunarodni Radio Srbija - 14/10/09)
